<TITLE> Man shot dead in Old Dhaka </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 4 (bdnews24.com)  A man was shot dead beside Bahadur Shah Park on Thursday in Old Dhaka. The dead, Prem Krishan Kumar, 40, was a goldsmith, police said. He was shot by unidentified gunmen on the northern side of the park at around 8am, said Shariful Islam, sub-inspector of Sutrapur Police Station. Doctors declared him dead when locals took him to Dhaka Medical College Hospital. Prem, who used to do business with his brother, was shot when he was returning after dropping his niece at her school. The motive of the killing is still unknown, said police. The investigation is going on, said Islam. 
